{"word":"G948 - βδελύσσω - bdelýssō - bdel-oos'-so - Abhor","sections":[{"paragraph":""},{"paragraph":"<strong>மூல வார்த்தை / Original: </strong><span class=\"hebrewOrGreek\">βδελύσσω</span>"},{"paragraph":"<strong>எழுத்துமாற்றம் / Transliteration: </strong>bdelýssō"},{"paragraph":"<strong>ஒலிபெயர்ப்பு / Phonetic: </strong>bdel-oos'-so"},{"paragraph":"<strong>சுருக்க விளக்கம் / Short Definition: </strong>Abhor"},{"paragraph":""},{"paragraph":"வினைச்சொல் - அருவரு"},{"paragraph":""},{"paragraph":"to render foul, to cause to be abhorred"},{"paragraph":""},{"paragraph":"<span class=\"spacer\"></span>"},{"paragraph":"<span class=\"parts-of-speech\"><strong>Part(s) of speech:</strong> Verb / வினைச்சொல்</span>"},{"paragraph":"<span class=\"spacer\"></span>"},{"paragraph":"<span class=\"original-in-english\"><strong>ஆங்கில மூலம் / Original in English:</strong> From a (presumed) derivative of<b>&#x03B2;&#x03B4;&#x03B5;&#x0301;&#x03C9;</b> <b>bdeo&#x0304;</b> (to <i>stink</i>); to <i>be disgusted</i>, that is, (by implication) <i>detest</i> (especially of idolatry): - abhor, abominable."},{"paragraph":"<span class=\"spacer\"></span>"},{"paragraph":"<strong>Cognate:</strong> <a href=\"#/G946 - βδέλυγμα - bdélygma - bdel'-oog-mah/946\">G946</a>, <a href=\"#/G947 - βδελυκτός - bdelyktós - bdel-ook-tos'/947\">G947</a>, <a href=\"#/G948 - βδελύσσω - bdelýssō - bdel-oos'-so/948\">G948</a>"}]}